API Endpoints

1. Register User

Endpoint: /api/v1/register
Method: POST

Request Parameters:
username: The username of the new user.
password: The password for the new user.

Response:
success: new user added (if registration is successful)
fail: user already exists (if the user already exists)

Ex: POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/register?username=vasya&password=12345

2. Login User

Endpoint: /api/v1/login
Method: POST

Request Parameters:
username: The username of the user.
password: The password of the user.

Response:
success: user logged in (if login is successful)
fail: no such user (if the user does not exist)
fail: incorrect password (if the password is incorrect)
fail: already logged in (if the user is already logged in)

Ex: POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/login?username=vasya8&password=12345

3. Logout User

Endpoint: /api/v1/logout
Method: POST

Request Parameters:
username: The username of the user.

Response:
success: user logged out (if logout is successful)
fail: no such user (if the user does not exist)
fail: already logged out (if the user is not logged in)

Ex: POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/logout?username=vasya&password=12345
